/*
HAGIWO MOD2 Arcade Laser Ver1.0

  • One-shot arcade laser voice with a 12-shape wavetable morph oscillator
  • 3 potentiometers with PUSH/SW two-page editing
  • SW OFF : Decay / Decay Envelope / Wavetable Morph
  • SW ON  : Pitch Width / Pitch Envelope / End Pitch
  • Trigger input (GPIO 7) : rising edge starts one laser voice
  • PUSH button (GPIO 6) : alternate edit-page toggle, active LOW, with per-ADC soft takeover
  • Level input (GPIO 0) : HIGH around trigger/playback = output level × 0.5
  • LED (GPIO 5) : 10 ms trigger blink, dim 10% while editing SW ON page
  • Parameters are stored in on-board flash after PUSH press, delayed until audio is idle
  • Audio output uses 10-bit PWM at 31.25 kHz, scaled to use full PWM range
  • ADC DMA input + PWM DMA output + Dual Core processing
  • ADC DMA is re-armed from ADC0 each block to prevent ADC1/ADC2 channel-order drift

  --Pin assign---
POT1     A0       SW OFF: Decay, SW ON: Pitch Width
POT2     A1       SW OFF: Decay Envelope, SW ON: Pitch Envelope
POT3     A2       SW OFF: Wavetable Morph, SW ON: End Pitch, reversed ADC
IN1      GPIO7    Trig in, active HIGH, rising edge starts playback
IN2      GPIO0    Level input, active HIGH, HIGH around trigger/playback = output level × 0.5
CV       A2       Shared with POT3
OUT      GPIO1    Audio PWM output (10-bit)
BUTTON   GPIO6    Alternate edit-page toggle, active LOW, press edge toggles page
LED      GPIO5    10 ms trigger blink, 10% PWM while SW ON page
EEPROM   save 6 sound parameters, delayed Flash commit

